1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,560
 in the week ahead.

2
00:00:01,560 --> 00:00:05,040
 Father, we thank you for this in Jesus' name.

3
00:00:05,040 --> 00:00:05,880
 Everyone says.

4
00:00:05,880 --> 00:00:06,880
 - Amen.

5
00:00:06,880 --> 00:00:08,680
 - Amen, amen.

6
00:00:08,680 --> 00:00:10,460
 Have a seat, have a seat.

7
00:00:10,460 --> 00:00:11,400
 It's so good to be.

8
00:00:11,400 --> 00:00:12,360
 Why don't you say hi to someone

9
00:00:12,360 --> 00:00:14,320
 who's sitting next to you for a moment.

10
00:00:14,320 --> 00:00:15,900
 Welcome them to church.

11
00:00:15,900 --> 00:00:20,720
 So good.

12
00:00:20,720 --> 00:00:22,960
 I'm, my name's Andrew.

13
00:00:22,960 --> 00:00:24,680
 I'm one of the pastors here at the Vine.

14
00:00:24,680 --> 00:00:26,880
 And if you're relatively new to the church,

15
00:00:26,880 --> 00:00:29,640
 we're packed in here today with overflow as well.

16
00:00:29,640 --> 00:00:31,600
 Hi to everybody who's in the overflow.

17
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:33,400
 We're so glad you're a part of our community.

18
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:35,560
 Everybody joining us online.

19
00:00:35,560 --> 00:00:39,780
 My uncle and aunt actually are joining online here today.

20
00:00:39,780 --> 00:00:43,500
 So it's great to have Pam and Ken with us as well.

21
00:00:43,500 --> 00:00:47,900
 As I step into the pulpit here this morning,

22
00:00:47,900 --> 00:00:51,340
 I do so really sensing the importance

23
00:00:51,340 --> 00:00:54,280
 and the weight of the time of history

24
00:00:54,280 --> 00:00:55,880
 that I think we're in right now.

25
00:00:55,880 --> 00:01:00,280
 And in particular, the importance of our faith,

26
00:01:00,280 --> 00:01:04,680
 our belief in Jesus to actually really mean something

27
00:01:04,680 --> 00:01:05,840
 in the world right now.

28
00:01:05,840 --> 00:01:08,080
 'Cause I don't know about you,

29
00:01:08,080 --> 00:01:11,760
 but I think the world is in a really ugly place right now.

30
00:01:11,760 --> 00:01:13,540
 Anyone else sensing this?

31
00:01:13,540 --> 00:01:15,580
 I think we can see, we're looking at the news

32
00:01:15,580 --> 00:01:18,120
 and our social media feeds.

33
00:01:18,120 --> 00:01:20,680
 It's really easy for us to see that the world

34
00:01:20,680 --> 00:01:23,560
 is more volatile than it's ever been before.

35
00:01:23,560 --> 00:01:25,400
 I would say the world is more violent

36
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:27,440
 than it's been for a long time.

37
00:01:27,440 --> 00:01:28,760
 The world is more divided.

38
00:01:28,760 --> 00:01:30,400
 There is more hatred.

39
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:32,160
 There are more challenges.

40
00:01:32,160 --> 00:01:33,560
 I don't know about you, but it's like for me,

41
00:01:33,560 --> 00:01:34,840
 when I'm waking up in the morning,

42
00:01:34,840 --> 00:01:38,720
 I have to take a big deep breath before I open my phone,

43
00:01:38,720 --> 00:01:40,520
 before I jump on my social media feed

44
00:01:40,520 --> 00:01:41,880
 and take a look at the news.

45
00:01:41,880 --> 00:01:44,720
 'Cause I'm wondering, what is it gonna be today?

46
00:01:44,720 --> 00:01:46,360
 Anyone else feel that way at the moment?

47
00:01:46,360 --> 00:01:48,320
 Like what's the next shooting gonna be?

48
00:01:48,320 --> 00:01:50,720
 What's the next terrorist act going to be?

49
00:01:50,720 --> 00:01:52,960
 What's the next stupid thing

50
00:01:52,960 --> 00:01:55,400
 that some leader of some government's gonna say?

51
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:58,120
 And when we kind of sit in this,

52
00:01:58,120 --> 00:02:00,320
 we realize that it's not just one city

53
00:02:00,320 --> 00:02:02,400
 or one country or one culture.

54
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:04,400
 This is kind of a global thing

55
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:06,220
 that is happening at the moment.

56
00:02:06,220 --> 00:02:10,560
 And this should deeply challenge us as Christians.

57
00:02:10,560 --> 00:02:13,600
 In fact, when we're living in a time

58
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:15,480
 like we're experiencing right now,

59
00:02:15,480 --> 00:02:18,080
 where it really does feel like the world

60
00:02:18,080 --> 00:02:22,440
 is in a super difficult, challenging, dark and ugly place,

61
00:02:22,440 --> 00:02:27,440
 I think it asks of Christians a very specific question.

62
00:02:27,440 --> 00:02:31,080
 A question to which the answer

63
00:02:31,080 --> 00:02:34,640
 will not only shape the future of the church itself,

64
00:02:34,640 --> 00:02:39,160
 but actually shape the future of the world itself.

65
00:02:39,160 --> 00:02:40,540
 And here's that question.

66
00:02:40,540 --> 00:02:44,800
 What should we do as Christians

67
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:48,080
 when the world has gone crazy?

68
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:53,280
 When have you been asking yourself that question lately?

69
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:56,960
 Like what should we do as believers of Jesus?

70
00:02:56,960 --> 00:02:58,240
 As people where the scriptures say

71
00:02:58,240 --> 00:03:00,680
 that the same spirit that raised Jesus from the dead

72
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:01,800
 is inside of me.

73
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:03,800
 What should we do as Christians

74
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:06,840
 when the world around us seems to be as crazy

75
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:09,320
 as it is right now?

76
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:10,800
 And while I would put it to you

77
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:13,760
 that I think this is the most critical question

78
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:16,400
 that the global church should be asking right now,

79
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:17,280
 here's the thing.

80
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:19,040
 It is not the first time

81
00:03:19,040 --> 00:03:21,040
 the church has had to ask that question.

82
00:03:21,040 --> 00:03:24,920
 In fact, if you look back over human history

83
00:03:24,920 --> 00:03:27,640
 and particular over church history,

84
00:03:27,640 --> 00:03:29,280
 there have been many, many times

85
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:31,120
 where it feels like for Christians

86
00:03:31,120 --> 00:03:33,680
 that the world has spun out of control.

87
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:35,000
 Many times where it feels like the world

88
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:36,960
 is suddenly broken out from underneath us

89
00:03:36,960 --> 00:03:38,360
 and we're kind of floating

90
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:40,920
 and we're not sure if we got any solid ground

91
00:03:40,920 --> 00:03:43,440
 for us to land on.

92
00:03:43,440 --> 00:03:45,040
 The question about what Christians should do

93
00:03:45,040 --> 00:03:46,440
 when the world has gone crazy

94
00:03:46,440 --> 00:03:51,320
 is something Christians have been asking for 2000 years.

95
00:03:51,320 --> 00:03:54,280
 And I wanna show you as we start today

96
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:58,920
 how I would say there are four primary models

97
00:03:58,920 --> 00:04:02,400
 that church over church history has embraced

98
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:06,040
 as an answer to this question of what we should do

99
00:04:06,040 --> 00:04:08,000
 when the world goes crazy.

100
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:09,240
 Here's the first one.

101
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:12,480
 I would say it is to escape.

102
00:04:12,480 --> 00:04:14,880
 And in this idea through church history,

103
00:04:14,880 --> 00:04:17,000
 the reality has been is that the world

104
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:18,000
 looks something like this.

105
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:21,160
 The world is this depraved, broken, dark,

106
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:23,400
 kind of ruined place.

107
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:27,520
 And we as Christians, we find ourselves in a world

108
00:04:27,520 --> 00:04:29,520
 that's spinning out of control,

109
00:04:29,520 --> 00:04:31,080
 in a world that's getting uglier and uglier,

110
00:04:31,080 --> 00:04:33,040
 more divided, more hostile, more violent.

111
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:34,280
 And here's our thought.

112
00:04:34,280 --> 00:04:38,520
 Our thought is, can we just get out of it, please?

113
00:04:38,520 --> 00:04:41,920
 Like if we could just bungee jump out of this world

114
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:43,640
 and get up to heaven,

115
00:04:43,640 --> 00:04:46,400
 then finally everything will be okay.

116
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:47,920
 And through church history,

117
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:51,520
 there have been theologies that have helped the church

118
00:04:51,520 --> 00:04:54,800
 to think about what it will be when we get out

119
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:56,480
 of the ugliness of this world,

120
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:59,560
 that everything burns here so that we can go

121
00:04:59,560 --> 00:05:03,640
 and enjoy eternal life on some fluffy cloud up there.

122
00:05:03,640 --> 00:05:07,560
 This kind of thinking kind of came into the church

123
00:05:07,560 --> 00:05:09,640
 as early as the third century

124
00:05:09,640 --> 00:05:11,080
 through the monastic movement.

125
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:13,880
 Now the monastic movement had some fantastic things

126
00:05:13,880 --> 00:05:16,360
 about it and to it even to this day.

127
00:05:16,360 --> 00:05:18,480
 But the monastic movement at its heart was this idea

128
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:21,760
 of let's just get out of the impurity of this world

129
00:05:21,760 --> 00:05:24,440
 so that we can create something where we can find

130
00:05:24,440 --> 00:05:28,960
 just a solid place of purity amongst ourselves.

131
00:05:28,960 --> 00:05:31,520
 What we've seen in church history of the answers

132
00:05:31,520 --> 00:05:34,160
 of the question of what do we do when the world goes crazy?

133
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:36,640
 Let's just get out of here.

134
00:05:36,640 --> 00:05:40,880
 The next one that we've seen in church history

135
00:05:40,880 --> 00:05:43,320
 is this one that I like to call insulate.

136
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:47,200
 So on this one, it's not so much the escape,

137
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:49,120
 but it has the same kind of idea.

138
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:52,440
 Here's the world and the world is that dark and evil

139
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:53,800
 and broken place.

140
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:58,320
 And here are us Christians and we are in this world.

141
00:05:58,320 --> 00:06:00,200
 Whether we like it or not,

142
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:02,120
 the reality is we're in the world.

143
00:06:02,120 --> 00:06:03,600
 Didn't Jesus himself say,

144
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:06,640
 "I've called you to be in the world," right?

145
00:06:06,640 --> 00:06:07,920
 But then how does he follow that?

146
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:09,360
 What does he say?

147
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:10,200
 But not of the world.

148
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:11,760
 He said, "I want you to be in the world,

149
00:06:11,760 --> 00:06:13,360
 but not of the world."

150
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:16,000
 And so there's been a movement through church history

151
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:19,040
 where it's like, okay, we can't escape this thing.

152
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:21,520
 I guess we're here until we die.

153
00:06:21,520 --> 00:06:23,280
 But whilst we're here, what we're gonna do

154
00:06:23,280 --> 00:06:25,600
 is we're gonna insulate ourselves

155
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:27,480
 from the darkness and the brokenness

156
00:06:27,480 --> 00:06:30,200
 and the hurt and the pain and everything else in the world.

157
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:34,360
 If we can just keep the world out of our churches,

158
00:06:34,360 --> 00:06:35,840
 everything will be fine.

159
00:06:35,840 --> 00:06:39,880
 And this kind of thought of insulation was really big

160
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:41,760
 in like even just recent church history.

161
00:06:41,760 --> 00:06:43,880
 I would say in like the '80s and '90s

162
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:46,360
 where we saw the rise of Christian culture,

163
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:48,080
 particularly in the West.

164
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:51,000
 And it was like, let's just Christianize everything.

165
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:52,200
 We're gonna Christianize music,

166
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:53,480
 we're gonna Christianize movies,

167
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:55,040
 we're gonna Christianize TV shows,

168
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:56,320
 we're gonna Christianize education.

169
00:06:56,320 --> 00:06:58,120
 Everything's gonna be Christianized.

170
00:06:58,120 --> 00:07:00,240
 And if I'm a Christian and I have a family,

171
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:02,160
 I'm just gonna make sure my family exists

172
00:07:02,160 --> 00:07:07,160
 in a Christian bubble and this horrible world cannot enter.

173
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:09,560
 Are you with me?

174
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:11,160
 Insulate.

175
00:07:11,160 --> 00:07:13,440
 Now, what we've also seen through church history

176
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:16,880
 is this next one that I call control.

177
00:07:16,880 --> 00:07:18,240
 What do we do when the world

178
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:20,640
 seems to be spinning out of control?

179
00:07:20,640 --> 00:07:22,240
 Well, here's the response to this.

180
00:07:22,240 --> 00:07:25,000
 Again, the world is seen as this dark, terrible, horrible,

181
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:29,600
 it's overwhelmed by sin and brokenness and evil.

182
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:31,720
 But in this response, the response is no,

183
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:34,120
 we're not gonna escape, we're not gonna insulate.

184
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:36,080
 Instead, we're gonna fight back.

185
00:07:36,080 --> 00:07:38,240
 And we're gonna fight back by actually trying

186
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:40,720
 to completely turn all of this thing

187
00:07:40,720 --> 00:07:43,960
 into as much Christianity as possible.

188
00:07:43,960 --> 00:07:46,600
 And we're gonna take our Christian religion

189
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:50,440
 and we're gonna try and control everything else.

190
00:07:50,440 --> 00:07:51,880
 Now, in this approach,

191
00:07:51,880 --> 00:07:54,720
 the idea sounds good on the surface, doesn't it?

192
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:56,560
 These two feels a little bit like

193
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:58,240
 we're trying to escape everything.

194
00:07:58,240 --> 00:08:00,600
 This one though, on the surface, sounds good.

195
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:04,840
 We're just gonna try and turn the world into Christianity.

196
00:08:04,840 --> 00:08:08,120
 Now, even though it sounds good,

197
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:10,280
 here's the problem throughout church history.

198
00:08:10,280 --> 00:08:13,080
 The problem is, even though maybe the idea

199
00:08:13,080 --> 00:08:14,560
 of wanting to see all of our cities,

200
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:17,240
 all of our countries worship Jesus,

201
00:08:17,240 --> 00:08:20,400
 we've come to think that the only way that's going to happen

202
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:23,600
 is if we take control of the situation.

203
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:25,320
 And by taking control of the situation,

204
00:08:25,320 --> 00:08:27,600
 church history has shown us that we've done that

205
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:31,960
 by actually taking worldly mechanisms and worldly power

206
00:08:31,960 --> 00:08:34,280
 and thinking by using worldly power

207
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:38,480
 to try to Christianize a nation or Christianize a culture,

208
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:40,080
 that's the right way to go.

209
00:08:40,080 --> 00:08:43,280
 And unfortunately, what happens is we take worldly power

210
00:08:43,280 --> 00:08:45,600
 and we dress it up in Christian clothes.

211
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:47,920
 And we think that we just need

212
00:08:47,920 --> 00:08:50,160
 to legislate the kingdom of God.

213
00:08:50,160 --> 00:08:52,360
 It's more of a top-down approach

214
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:54,840
 where when you look at the role of Jesus

215
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:56,520
 and the life of Jesus

216
00:08:56,520 --> 00:08:58,680
 and what he tried to speak about with the disciples,

217
00:08:58,680 --> 00:09:00,960
 it was a bottom-up influence,

218
00:09:00,960 --> 00:09:04,520
 but this one says, no, we can do it top-down.

219
00:09:04,520 --> 00:09:09,640
 This happened in the late 11th century

220
00:09:09,640 --> 00:09:11,640
 with the beginning of the Crusades

221
00:09:11,640 --> 00:09:13,320
 and it's happened in many different ways.

222
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:16,280
 And I would argue is currently manifesting itself

223
00:09:16,280 --> 00:09:18,760
 a little bit in some countries in our world

224
00:09:18,760 --> 00:09:21,240
 with the rise of Christian nationalism.

225
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:27,160
 The fourth one is this idea of conform.

226
00:09:27,160 --> 00:09:30,360
 So when the world spins out of control and gets crazy,

227
00:09:30,360 --> 00:09:31,480
 what are we going to do?

228
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:32,640
 Well, here's what we're gonna do.

229
00:09:32,640 --> 00:09:35,600
 Yes, the world is broken, it's bad, it's hurting,

230
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:36,800
 there's a lot of suffering,

231
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:38,760
 and we are Christians in that world,

232
00:09:38,760 --> 00:09:41,560
 but you know what?

233
00:09:41,560 --> 00:09:44,520
 Let's just not rock the boat a little bit here.

234
00:09:44,520 --> 00:09:46,440
 Let's just, we think that Christianity

235
00:09:46,440 --> 00:09:47,640
 has something to say to the world,

236
00:09:47,640 --> 00:09:50,360
 but let's just be nice.

237
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:52,600
 Let's just make sure that we're not rocking the boat,

238
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:54,480
 we're not doing anything crazy,

239
00:09:54,480 --> 00:09:56,680
 we're not doing anything that might get us into trouble.

240
00:09:56,680 --> 00:09:58,200
 In fact, why don't we just make sure

241
00:09:58,200 --> 00:10:00,120
 that everybody likes us?

242
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:02,120
 And if everybody likes us,

243
00:10:02,120 --> 00:10:04,480
 then everything's gonna be okay, surely.

244
00:10:04,480 --> 00:10:05,720
 Like, that's what we want.

245
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:08,560
 And so what we do is we end up turning our churches

246
00:10:08,560 --> 00:10:12,560
 into places that feel exactly like the world.

247
00:10:12,560 --> 00:10:15,400
 And rather than standing on some of the beliefs

248
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:16,960
 that we have and some of the scriptures that we have

249
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:18,520
 and some of the ways in which we are supposed

250
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:21,960
 to be different, living a different, renewed story

251
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:23,520
 in the world around us,

252
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:25,320
 we actually begin to look more like the world

253
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:26,600
 than the world does.

254
00:10:27,520 --> 00:10:31,120
 And we have found ourselves in a place of compromise,

255
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:33,640
 in a place of kind of consolidating ourselves

256
00:10:33,640 --> 00:10:34,480
 into the world.

257
00:10:34,480 --> 00:10:37,760
 And the reality is the world begins to shape the church

258
00:10:37,760 --> 00:10:39,920
 more than the church is shaping the world.

259
00:10:39,920 --> 00:10:42,000
 And when that takes place,

260
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:43,480
 now this happened in Jesus' time,

261
00:10:43,480 --> 00:10:46,640
 the Sadducees, the Jewish Sadducees were this mindset.

262
00:10:46,640 --> 00:10:48,160
 Let's just try to get on with the Romans,

263
00:10:48,160 --> 00:10:50,680
 let's try and kind of work with the Romans

264
00:10:50,680 --> 00:10:53,040
 and maybe God will come and do something amazing.

265
00:10:53,040 --> 00:10:56,200
 And from that time on, I think this happens an awful lot.

266
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:58,640
 So I want you to see two things

