00:12:26,680 --> 00:12:28,720
 Can you do that for me for a second?

304
00:12:28,720 --> 00:12:30,680
 Just have a think about that.

305
00:12:30,680 --> 00:12:34,440
 Are you one that's more likely to escape, insulate,

306
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:39,440
 try to control your environments or try to conform to it?

307
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:42,360
 That's the first thing.

308
00:12:42,360 --> 00:12:44,120
 Here's the second thing.

309
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:47,480
 I want you to see that three fourths of these,

310
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:49,160
 three quarters of these

311
00:12:49,160 --> 00:12:51,760
 are basically the response of Christianity

312
00:12:51,760 --> 00:12:56,760
 to remain private in a time when the world is falling apart.

313
00:12:56,760 --> 00:13:00,640
 Notice this, escape, insulate, and conform

314
00:13:00,640 --> 00:13:02,680
 are essentially Christians

315
00:13:02,680 --> 00:13:05,960
 taking what Christ has done in their lives,

316
00:13:05,960 --> 00:13:07,960
 taking all the things that Christ has renewed

317
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:08,800
 and done in them,

318
00:13:08,800 --> 00:13:10,960
 the Holy Spirit that is placed within them,

319
00:13:10,960 --> 00:13:14,200
 taking all of that and remaining private about it

320
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:15,680
 rather than allowing those things

321
00:13:15,680 --> 00:13:19,080
 to have some sort of public impact around them.

322
00:13:19,080 --> 00:13:21,520
 It fascinates me that the church through history

323
00:13:21,520 --> 00:13:25,400
 has embraced privatization of faith

324
00:13:25,400 --> 00:13:30,400
 over the engagement of the culture in which it is planted.

325
00:13:30,400 --> 00:13:33,680
 And this is significant

326
00:13:33,680 --> 00:13:35,840
 because I think that this is not just something

327
00:13:35,840 --> 00:13:37,960
 that we see in church history,

328
00:13:37,960 --> 00:13:39,280
 if I'm honest with you,

329
00:13:39,280 --> 00:13:42,040
 I think it's something that we all struggle with today.

330
00:13:42,040 --> 00:13:44,840
 I think when things get hard,

331
00:13:44,840 --> 00:13:46,480
 when we find things challenging,

332
00:13:46,480 --> 00:13:48,000
 when everybody in our office

333
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:50,160
 is talking about the craziness of the world,

334
00:13:50,160 --> 00:13:55,160
 it's much more easy for us to conform to that conversation

335
00:13:55,160 --> 00:13:57,680
 than to stand apart to it.

336
00:13:57,680 --> 00:14:00,200
 It's much easier for us

337
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:04,520
 to actually just kind of keep our faith to ourselves

338
00:14:04,520 --> 00:14:06,480
 at the very moment

339
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:09,440
 when the world needs that faith the most.

340
00:14:09,440 --> 00:14:12,200
 Think of it this way,

341
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:14,320
 I think one of the greatest temptations

342
00:14:14,320 --> 00:14:15,880
 that we have as the church

343
00:14:15,880 --> 00:14:18,080
 when the world goes crazy is this,

344
00:14:18,080 --> 00:14:20,000
 to privatize our faith

345
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:22,080
 and actually move more inward

346
00:14:22,080 --> 00:14:24,560
 rather than outward with what we believe.

347
00:14:24,560 --> 00:14:26,840
 I mean, can you imagine

348
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:29,200
 that that has been the response through history

349
00:14:29,200 --> 00:14:31,040
 that we would in times that are difficult

350
00:14:31,040 --> 00:14:33,960
 more go inward with our faith

351
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:36,600
 than outward with the very thing

352
00:14:36,600 --> 00:14:40,320
 that can help the broken world around us.

353
00:14:40,320 --> 00:14:44,640
 Escape, insulate, conform, whatever it might be.

354
00:14:44,640 --> 00:14:47,480
 But that private response

355
00:14:47,480 --> 00:14:50,600
 is what we wanna challenge over the next seven weeks.

356
00:14:50,600 --> 00:14:55,600
 Because that privacy is alive in all of us, I would argue.

357
00:14:55,600 --> 00:14:58,280
 And I wanna challenge you with that as well.

358
00:14:58,280 --> 00:14:59,480
 I mean, think about it for a moment,

359
00:14:59,480 --> 00:15:04,480
 do you feel like you quite often compartmentalize your faith?

360
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:07,000
 Finding yourself super Christian

361
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:09,600
 when you're in the right environment with the right people

362
00:15:09,600 --> 00:15:13,040
 and finding yourself super quiet about it

363
00:15:13,040 --> 00:15:14,520
 when you're in a different position

364
00:15:14,520 --> 00:15:16,720
 or a different community.

365
00:15:16,720 --> 00:15:17,960
 And it's interesting when this happens

366
00:15:17,960 --> 00:15:19,520
 because you're probably sitting there thinking like,

367
00:15:19,520 --> 00:15:20,800
 I don't know if I do that Pastor Andrew,

368
00:15:20,800 --> 00:15:21,640
 I don't know if that's for me,

369
00:15:21,640 --> 00:15:22,760
 that's a word for my neighbor

370
00:15:22,760 --> 00:15:24,880
 sitting right next to me right now.

371
00:15:24,880 --> 00:15:27,400
 Like that's a great word for them, but I think I'm fine.

372
00:15:27,400 --> 00:15:28,680
 I don't think I privatize my faith.

373
00:15:28,680 --> 00:15:30,520
 Do I privatize my faith?

374
00:15:30,520 --> 00:15:31,640
 Let me just be honest,

375
00:15:31,640 --> 00:15:33,520
 in a lot of the conversations that I have with us

376
00:15:33,520 --> 00:15:34,360
 here at the Vine

377
00:15:34,360 --> 00:15:35,520
 and conversations I have with other Christians

378
00:15:35,520 --> 00:15:36,360
 and other churches,

379
00:15:36,360 --> 00:15:38,720
 here's some things that I hear from us

380
00:15:38,720 --> 00:15:42,160
 that I think moves us towards private faith

381
00:15:42,160 --> 00:15:43,200
 rather than public faith.

382
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:44,280
 Let me share a few of these.

383
00:15:44,280 --> 00:15:45,880
 Here's the first one.

384
00:15:45,880 --> 00:15:48,520
 My faith is just very personal to me.

385
00:15:48,520 --> 00:15:51,760
 I hear Christians say this all the time.

386
00:15:51,760 --> 00:15:54,680
 My faith is just really personal to me.

387
00:15:54,680 --> 00:15:56,000
 Oh, it's so personal to me.

388
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:57,120
 Christ has saved me

389
00:15:57,120 --> 00:15:59,840
 and he saved me from this terrible time in my life

390
00:15:59,840 --> 00:16:02,160
 and it's just so deeply personal

391
00:16:02,160 --> 00:16:03,840
 and deeply intimate with him.

392
00:16:03,840 --> 00:16:05,440
 And I just am so grateful

393
00:16:05,440 --> 00:16:07,920
 that I have this private, personal,

394
00:16:07,920 --> 00:16:09,720
 intimate relationship with him.

395
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:10,880
 And to be honest with you,

396
00:16:10,880 --> 00:16:13,160
 I'm pretty happy with that relationship.

397
00:16:13,160 --> 00:16:14,480
 So happy in fact,

398
00:16:14,480 --> 00:16:17,440
 that if I shared it or I allowed others into it,

399
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:20,000
 it would probably pollute what I have.

400
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:22,200
 And because of that, we stay,

401
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:23,200
 it's almost like this.

402
00:16:23,200 --> 00:16:26,120
 It's like you discover a restaurant in Hong Kong

403
00:16:26,120 --> 00:16:27,760
 and it's an amazing restaurant.

404
00:16:27,760 --> 00:16:30,320
 The food is incredible and it's super cheap.

405
00:16:30,320 --> 00:16:31,480
 And you're sitting there thinking,

406
00:16:31,480 --> 00:16:34,360
 I hope nobody finds out about this restaurant.

407
00:16:34,360 --> 00:16:36,120
 I hope nobody finds out about this restaurant

408
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:38,240
 because if they do, it will get ruined.

409
00:16:38,240 --> 00:16:40,560
 When we say as Christians,

410
00:16:40,560 --> 00:16:42,840
 my faith is just really personal to me.

411
00:16:42,840 --> 00:16:44,480
 What we're essentially saying

412
00:16:44,480 --> 00:16:48,520
 is that I wanna keep it personal

413
00:16:48,520 --> 00:16:50,080
 because I think if I shared it,

414
00:16:50,080 --> 00:16:52,840
 I would lose something of its value to me.

415
00:16:52,840 --> 00:16:54,480
 And I wanna put it to you just this,

416
00:16:54,480 --> 00:16:55,560
 I'm gonna be honest,

417
00:16:55,560 --> 00:16:57,000
 that's incredibly selfish.

418
00:16:57,000 --> 00:17:00,560
 Here's another thing we say, we say this.

419
00:17:00,560 --> 00:17:03,320
 We say, well, every person has the right to believe

420
00:17:03,320 --> 00:17:05,240
 what they wanna believe.

421
00:17:05,240 --> 00:17:06,760
 And that's absolutely right.

422
00:17:06,760 --> 00:17:09,920
 I mean, that is what a good, open and free society

423
00:17:09,920 --> 00:17:10,840
 should be built on.

424
00:17:10,840 --> 00:17:13,480
 We should want everybody to have the freedom

425
00:17:13,480 --> 00:17:15,680
 to believe what it is that they've been called to believe.

426
00:17:15,680 --> 00:17:17,720
 And that means that I have the freedom to believe

427
00:17:17,720 --> 00:17:19,800
 that Lord Jesus Christ is my personal savior

428
00:17:19,800 --> 00:17:20,680
 here in Hong Kong.

429
00:17:20,680 --> 00:17:21,760
 That is an amazing thing.

430
00:17:21,760 --> 00:17:25,720
 People should be free to believe what they want to believe.

431
00:17:25,720 --> 00:17:28,040
 Now, in a true statement like that,

432
00:17:28,040 --> 00:17:29,400
 here's the issue with it though,

433
00:17:29,400 --> 00:17:30,800
 I think for us Christians,

434
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:33,760
 is that there's some baggage that comes alongside of it,

435
00:17:33,760 --> 00:17:36,480
 some broader thinking that comes alongside of it.

436
00:17:36,480 --> 00:17:37,560
 And here's that thinking,

437
00:17:37,560 --> 00:17:40,640
 it's this culture, you do you.

438
00:17:40,640 --> 00:17:42,240
 I'll do me.

439
00:17:42,240 --> 00:17:43,680
 Like you do you.

440
00:17:43,680 --> 00:17:46,000
 Like Alison, I'm totally cool with you doing you, man.

441
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:47,600
 You got a baby strapped around you right now.

442
00:17:47,600 --> 00:17:49,240
 Like you do you, Alison.

443
00:17:49,240 --> 00:17:50,680
 I'm gonna do me, right?

444
00:17:50,680 --> 00:17:51,880
 And you're happy with me being me,

445
00:17:51,880 --> 00:17:54,600
 I'm happy with you being you, go for it, girl.

446
00:17:54,600 --> 00:17:57,720
 What that's basically saying is, you keep you private,

447
00:17:57,720 --> 00:18:00,400
 I keep me private, and that's the way we're gonna be.

448
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:01,320
 We're just gonna live like that.

449
00:18:01,320 --> 00:18:02,320
 I'm never gonna challenge you,

450
00:18:02,320 --> 00:18:03,320
 I'm never gonna debate with you,

451
00:18:03,320 --> 00:18:05,280
 I'm just gonna go, no, no, no, no, that's you.

452
00:18:05,280 --> 00:18:07,000
 You do you, right?

453
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:07,880
 And what that does,

454
00:18:07,880 --> 00:18:10,480
 even though we think we're saying the right thing,

455
00:18:10,480 --> 00:18:13,240
 what that ultimately does is cause us as Christians

456
00:18:13,240 --> 00:18:15,440
 to keep our part private.

457
00:18:15,440 --> 00:18:20,720
 Or maybe we say this, I'm not blank enough yet.

458
00:18:20,720 --> 00:18:23,080
 So I'm not gonna share my faith

459
00:18:23,080 --> 00:18:25,040
 because I'm not blank enough yet.

460
00:18:25,040 --> 00:18:27,400
 I'm not maybe wise enough yet.

461
00:18:27,400 --> 00:18:29,520
 I'm not experienced enough yet.

462
00:18:29,520 --> 00:18:32,320
 I haven't had as many years as a Christian enough yet.

463
00:18:32,320 --> 00:18:34,440
 I don't understand the Bible enough yet.

464
00:18:34,440 --> 00:18:36,760
 I'm not strong enough or brave, whatever it is,

465
00:18:36,760 --> 00:18:40,520
 we place so many excuses in the blank space there.

466
00:18:40,520 --> 00:18:41,400
 And we say, no, no, no,

467
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:43,240
 I'm gonna just keep my faith private.

468
00:18:43,240 --> 00:18:47,200
 And so I feel I'm super equipped and ready to share it.

469
00:18:47,200 --> 00:18:49,400
 When we do that, people are walking past us

470
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:54,200
 every single day, crying out for more hope in a dark world.

471
00:18:54,200 --> 00:18:55,320
 And you're there going,

472
00:18:55,320 --> 00:18:58,200
 I don't think I understand revelations enough yet.

473
00:18:58,200 --> 00:19:03,780
 When the gospel sits inside of you and is dying to get out.

474
00:19:04,760 --> 00:19:07,040
 I think sometimes we also say this,

475
00:19:07,040 --> 00:19:10,700
 I'm embarrassed by what other Christians do publicly.

476
00:19:10,700 --> 00:19:13,560
 This is the one that I resonate most with.

477
00:19:13,560 --> 00:19:14,760
 I'm just being honest with you.

478
00:19:14,760 --> 00:19:16,400
 There's some stuff in my feeds

479
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:18,320
 that I've seen in the last couple of weeks

480
00:19:18,320 --> 00:19:20,360
 of Christian pastors and people I know,

481
00:19:20,360 --> 00:19:22,400
 Christians and people that I follow

482
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:24,720
 who are representing a version of Christianity

483
00:19:24,720 --> 00:19:26,480
 that to me is abhorrent.

484
00:19:26,480 --> 00:19:30,760
 And when I see that, here's my response.

485
00:19:30,760 --> 00:19:32,360
 It's not, I need to get out there

486
00:19:32,360 --> 00:19:34,280
 that represent a better view of Christianity.

487
00:19:34,280 --> 00:19:37,580
 It's me going, I hope no one thinks that my faith is that.

488
00:19:37,580 --> 00:19:40,000
 Are you with me?

489
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:41,240
 And when we start to think like that,

490
00:19:41,240 --> 00:19:42,760
 here's what our tendency is.

491
00:19:42,760 --> 00:19:45,160
 I'm just gonna sort of separate myself

492
00:19:45,160 --> 00:19:46,840
 from all this Christian talk stuff

493
00:19:46,840 --> 00:19:47,760
 'cause I don't want people to think

494
00:19:47,760 --> 00:19:50,760
 that my Jesus is that Jesus.

495
00:19:50,760 --> 00:19:54,000
 So I'm gonna be very private and keep to myself

496
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:55,520
 and just keep believing what I believe.

497
00:19:55,520 --> 00:19:56,520
 And I'm just gonna whatever.

498
00:19:56,520 --> 00:19:59,140
 And I'm just so embarrassed or angry or shamed

499
00:19:59,140 --> 00:20:00,560
 by what they're presenting.

500
00:20:00,560 --> 00:20:02,280
 I just don't wanna present anything

501
00:20:02,280 --> 00:20:03,880
 'cause I don't wanna be associated with it at all.

502
00:20:03,880 --> 00:20:05,560
 Okay, are you following this?

503
00:20:05,560 --> 00:20:09,540
 So we do these things and this is how privacy in our faith

504
00:20:09,540 --> 00:20:11,000
 begins to grip inside of us.

505
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:13,440
 And when this happens, here's what will happen.

506
00:20:13,440 --> 00:20:17,640
 You will end up living a dualistic Christian faith

507
00:20:17,640 --> 00:20:20,200
 where you'll be super pumped up for Jesus

508
00:20:20,200 --> 00:20:22,560
 on a Sunday in a gathering like this,

509
00:20:22,560 --> 00:20:26,600
 but then Monday to Saturday, no one would ever know.

510
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:28,920
 And you'll justify it by saying, it's personal to me.

511
00:20:28,920 --> 00:20:30,080
 Have you seen what they're doing?

512
00:20:30,080 --> 00:20:31,560
 I don't wanna be associated with that.

513
00:20:31,560 --> 00:20:33,800
 Or justify it with I'm not X enough yet

514
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:35,360
 or whatever it might be.

515
00:20:35,360 --> 00:20:37,200
 But we'll end up living this dualistic life.

516
00:20:37,200 --> 00:20:40,280
 Here's what fascinates me about this idea

517
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:42,060
 that we as Christians generally like

518
00:20:42,060 --> 00:20:43,860
 to keep our faith private.

519
00:20:43,860 --> 00:20:47,560
 It's actually interesting because all of the other

520
00:20:47,560 --> 00:20:51,120
 intimate relationships in our lives, we love to proclaim.

521
00:20:51,120 --> 00:20:54,160
 Like take a look at your social media feed.

522
00:20:54,160 --> 00:20:56,480
 Your social media feed that you put out in the world

523
00:20:56,480 --> 00:20:58,720
 will primarily be, look at my baby.

524
00:20:59,760 --> 00:21:02,480
 Or look at my husband, look at my wife.

525
00:21:02,480 --> 00:21:04,440
 We just celebrated my daughter's 15th birthday.

526
00:21:04,440 --> 00:21:05,280
 It was awesome.

527
00:21:05,280 --> 00:21:06,120
 Look at me, I'm 15.

528
00:21:06,120 --> 00:21:07,920
 Woo-hoo, there's a cake and family

529
00:21:07,920 --> 00:21:09,720
 and we love each other, right?

530
00:21:09,720 --> 00:21:13,240
 So the relationships that are super intimate to us

531
00:21:13,240 --> 00:21:15,360
 that we find very personal and whatever,

532
00:21:15,360 --> 00:21:18,120
 all of those relationships, we long to put out there

533
00:21:18,120 --> 00:21:20,640
 into the public sphere so that other people can see

534
00:21:20,640 --> 00:21:22,480
 that we have a great family, we have a great relationship,

535
00:21:22,480 --> 00:21:23,960
 great marriage, whatever it might be.

536
00:21:23,960 --> 00:21:26,120
 These are the things that are valuable to me

537
00:21:26,120 --> 00:21:28,400
 and I'm putting it out there for the world to see.

538
00:21:28,400 --> 00:21:31,560
 But as Christians with our relationship with Jesus,

539
00:21:31,560 --> 00:21:33,440
 why is it that we so often walk

540
00:21:33,440 --> 00:21:36,080
 in the opposite spirit to that?

541
00:21:36,080 --> 00:21:37,400
 Fascinates me.

542
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:40,720
 It also fascinates me that here, I've come to realize this,

543
00:21:40,720 --> 00:21:45,080
 that the relationships that we often want to keep private

544
00:21:45,080 --> 00:21:48,740
 are usually the relationships that we know are wrong.

545
00:21:48,740 --> 00:21:51,740
 Come on.

546
00:21:51,740 --> 00:21:53,960
 Like we know they're wrong.

547
00:21:53,960 --> 00:21:56,080
 We know we shouldn't be doing that.

548
00:21:56,080 --> 00:21:59,440
 We wanna keep that private because if our boss found it out,

549
00:21:59,440 --> 00:22:00,400
 we'd get fired.

550
00:22:00,400 --> 00:22:02,600
 If our wife or our spouse found it out,

551
00:22:02,600 --> 00:22:03,840
 we'd probably get divorced.

552
00:22:03,840 --> 00:22:05,960
 And so the stuff that we know is wrong,

553
00:22:05,960 --> 00:22:07,760
 we deem to keep private.

554
00:22:07,760 --> 00:22:09,640
 The stuff we want people to think about us,

555
00:22:09,640 --> 00:22:12,680
 we want to bring public, but when it comes to the church

556
00:22:12,680 --> 00:22:15,200
 and when the world becomes a dumpster fire,

557
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:18,680
 we retreat rather than engage.

558
00:22:18,680 --> 00:22:24,400
 And when we do this, I'm not just talking about

559
00:22:24,400 --> 00:22:28,440
 the reality of sharing the gospel and evangelizing Jesus.

560
00:22:28,440 --> 00:22:30,720
 I'm also talking about the fact that we often keep

561
00:22:30,720 --> 00:22:34,000
 as Christians private very much our values,

562
00:22:34,000 --> 00:22:36,680
 very much our behaviors, very much the things

563
00:22:36,680 --> 00:22:39,360
 that Christ is doing in a process of sanctification

564
00:22:39,360 --> 00:22:42,240
 in our lives, making us more and more like Christ Jesus.

565
00:22:42,240 --> 00:22:44,580
 That stuff we also suppress.

566
00:22:44,580 --> 00:22:47,480
 The very stuff that changes our thinking,

567
00:22:47,480 --> 00:22:49,780
 changes our decisions, changes our habits,

568
00:22:49,780 --> 00:22:53,000
 that should be shaping and molding us to show the world

569
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:54,560
 the hands and feet of Jesus.

570
00:22:54,560 --> 00:22:56,800
 This stuff we also keep quiet.

571
00:22:56,800 --> 00:22:59,400
 It's not just, I wanna tell you about Jesus Christ.

572
00:22:59,400 --> 00:23:03,320
 It's also more compassion, more love, more humility,

573
00:23:03,320 --> 00:23:08,080
 more servant heartedness, even that we somehow keep private.

574
00:23:08,080 --> 00:23:11,560
 When the Holy Spirit has taught us and changed us

575
00:23:11,560 --> 00:23:14,880
 and has called us to live for him in such a way

576
00:23:14,880 --> 00:23:16,760
 that we need to understand that when the calling

577
00:23:16,760 --> 00:23:18,540
 is to a more public faith,

578
00:23:18,540 --> 00:23:20,920
 it's not just for individual benefit.

579
00:23:22,320 --> 00:23:25,240
 When we're called to a more public faith,

580
00:23:25,240 --> 00:23:28,520
 it's so that we might show the love of Christ to the world,

581
00:23:28,520 --> 00:23:31,680
 not just with our words, but also with our actions,

582
00:23:31,680 --> 00:23:35,200
 with our decisions, with our habits, with our character,

583
00:23:35,200 --> 00:23:38,440
 and with the things that we also say.

584
00:23:38,440 --> 00:23:41,240
 And in doing that, people begin to see something

585
00:23:41,240 --> 00:23:43,260
 that in the darkness of the world,

586
00:23:43,260 --> 00:23:46,480
 before that they were not able to see.

587
00:23:46,480 --> 00:23:51,120
 This is why when we think about our response

588
00:23:51,120 --> 00:23:54,120
 through church history, we can understand

589
00:23:54,120 --> 00:23:57,080
 that the way is not to escape.

590
00:23:57,080 --> 00:24:00,680
 The way has to be to lean in and to engage,

591
00:24:00,680 --> 00:24:03,620
 but that has to be not through a worldly empire

592
00:24:03,620 --> 00:24:05,740
 and a worldly power model.

593
00:24:05,740 --> 00:24:08,340
 There has to be a better way.

594
00:24:08,340 --> 00:24:13,900
 There has to be another way to engage this world

595
00:24:13,900 --> 00:24:16,160
 that truly brings it to life.

596
00:24:16,160 --> 00:24:19,960
 Dietrich Bonhoeffer writing at the time

597
00:24:19,960 --> 00:24:23,560
 where the world really was a dumpster fire.

598
00:24:23,560 --> 00:24:26,680
 In the time of the rise of Nazi Germany

599
00:24:26,680 --> 00:24:28,880
 as a German Christian himself,

600
00:24:28,880 --> 00:24:31,440
 looking at the church around him

601
00:24:31,440 --> 00:24:34,960
 and seeing how conforming the church was

602
00:24:34,960 --> 00:24:37,560
 to a significant moment in history,

603
00:24:37,560 --> 00:24:39,960
 Bonhoeffer wrote this.

604
00:24:39,960 --> 00:24:41,760
 He said, "Any community of Jesus

605
00:24:41,760 --> 00:24:44,560
 "which wants to be invisible or dominant

606
00:24:44,560 --> 00:24:48,000
 "is no longer a community that follows him."

607
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:54,000
 The prophet Bonhoeffer is speaking into our time today,

608
00:24:54,000 --> 00:24:56,600
 I believe.

609
00:24:56,600 --> 00:24:59,120
 As we see all the challenges that are around us,

610
00:24:59,120 --> 00:25:02,080
 this is the deep question we need to be asking ourselves.

611
00:25:02,080 --> 00:25:05,080
 Is there a better way than this?

612
00:25:05,080 --> 00:25:08,140
 And if there is, what does it look like?

613
00:25:08,140 --> 00:25:11,800
 And that's what the next seven weeks are about.

614
00:25:11,800 --> 00:25:12,760
 I'm done, would you stand with me?

615
00:25:12,760 --> 00:25:15,100
 I'm gonna put, no, just don't stand.

616
00:25:15,100 --> 00:25:16,520
 But that's what the next seven weeks are about.

617
00:25:16,520 --> 00:25:17,580
 We wanna open up for you.

618
00:25:17,580 --> 00:25:19,200
 What is the better way?

619
00:25:19,200 --> 00:25:22,680
 There is in my mind, another model.

620
00:25:22,680 --> 00:25:24,880
 There is the model that we see in the life, death

621
00:25:24,880 --> 00:25:26,440
 and resurrection of Jesus,

622
00:25:26,440 --> 00:25:29,720
 the manifesto of Christ that he brings into the world

623
00:25:29,720 --> 00:25:32,160
 and says, this is the way we should be.

624
00:25:32,160 --> 00:25:34,880
 Even if there's an empire, even if there's oppression,

625
00:25:34,880 --> 00:25:37,840
 even if there's persecution, even if there's injustice,

626
00:25:37,840 --> 00:25:39,600
 even if there's the darkness and the hatred

627
00:25:39,600 --> 00:25:41,280
 and the bigotry and everything like that,

628
00:25:41,280 --> 00:25:45,080
 even when that's alive, this is how we should be

629
00:25:45,080 --> 00:25:47,940
 as the church, as believers in Jesus.

630
00:25:47,940 --> 00:25:52,220
 What we see in the life of Christ is a new and fresh way.

631
00:25:52,220 --> 00:25:54,460
 And so what I wanna do this morning

632
00:25:54,460 --> 00:25:57,380
 is I wanna just start the process of shining a light

633
00:25:57,380 --> 00:25:58,660
 onto this new way.

634
00:25:58,660 --> 00:26:01,260
 And over these next seven weeks, we're gonna unpack that

635
00:26:01,260 --> 00:26:03,280
 as we look at different spheres of influence

636
00:26:03,280 --> 00:26:05,300
 that each one of us has in our lives

637
00:26:05,300 --> 00:26:09,140
 and how we can be living more publicly for Christ

638
00:26:09,140 --> 00:26:10,980
 in those spaces.

639
00:26:10,980 --> 00:26:13,180
 There's a passage at the beginning

640
00:26:13,180 --> 00:26:14,860
 of the Sermon of the Mount.

641
00:26:14,860 --> 00:26:18,820
 Jesus' manifesto of how Christians should be in this world

642
00:26:18,820 --> 00:26:22,420
 from Matthew 5-7, but there's a bit just at the start of it

643
00:26:22,420 --> 00:26:25,980
 where he speaks directly to how we should be

644
00:26:25,980 --> 00:26:28,060
 when the world has gone crazy.

645
00:26:28,060 --> 00:26:29,820
 And when he's writing this or saying it

646
00:26:29,820 --> 00:26:33,500
 in the original time, it was a crazy world with that empire.

647
00:26:33,500 --> 00:26:35,560
 But even the readers, the first readers

648
00:26:35,560 --> 00:26:39,780
 of the Gospel of Matthew, who probably in about 70-75 AD

649
00:26:39,780 --> 00:26:42,660
 had just seen what Nero had done as the emperor

650
00:26:42,660 --> 00:26:45,460
 in destroying the temple, killing many Christians,

651
00:26:45,460 --> 00:26:47,780
 and then reading this and thinking, hang on a sec,

652
00:26:47,780 --> 00:26:51,300
 we want to escape this Greek or Roman empire right now.

653
00:26:51,300 --> 00:26:53,680
 We want to insulate ourselves.

654
00:26:53,680 --> 00:26:56,900
 But even into that moment, here's what Jesus says.

655
00:26:56,900 --> 00:26:59,260
 He's like, you wanna know how to be?

656
00:26:59,260 --> 00:27:00,100
 Here it is.

657
00:27:00,100 --> 00:27:05,460
 You are salt of the earth.

658
00:27:05,460 --> 00:27:07,180
 But if the salt loses its saltiness,

659
00:27:07,180 --> 00:27:08,900
 how can it be made salty again?

660
00:27:08,900 --> 00:27:10,260
 It is no longer good for anything

661
00:27:10,260 --> 00:27:13,180
 except to be thrown out and trampled by people.

662
00:27:13,180 --> 00:27:15,020
 For you are the light of the world.

663
00:27:15,020 --> 00:27:17,580
 A city on a hill cannot be hidden.

664
00:27:17,580 --> 00:27:20,460
 Neither do people light a lamp and put it under a bowl.

665
00:27:20,460 --> 00:27:22,100
 Instead, they put it on its stand

666
00:27:22,100 --> 00:27:24,900
 and it gives light to everyone in the house.

667
00:27:24,900 --> 00:27:29,660
 So in the same way, let your light shine before all people,

668
00:27:29,660 --> 00:27:32,580
 that they may see your good deeds

669
00:27:32,580 --> 00:27:35,700
 and praise your Father in heaven.

670
00:27:35,700 --> 00:27:39,140
 Jesus' response to what Christians should do

671
00:27:39,140 --> 00:27:41,700
 when the world goes crazy,

672
00:27:41,700 --> 00:27:45,060
 simply says you are salt and you are light.

673
00:27:45,060 --> 00:27:46,300
 And in these two metaphors,

674
00:27:46,300 --> 00:27:50,820
 he unpacks for us a new and better way.

675
00:27:50,820 --> 00:27:52,100
 Let me just break them down real quick.

676
00:27:52,100 --> 00:27:54,180
 Salt, in Jesus' time,

677
00:27:54,180 --> 00:27:56,780
 salt really carried three specific things.

678
00:27:56,780 --> 00:27:58,580
 Preachers of this passage have come up

679
00:27:58,580 --> 00:28:00,900
 with multiple expressions of what salt can do

680
00:28:00,900 --> 00:28:01,740
 and all that.

681
00:28:01,740 --> 00:28:02,700
 But actually, when you think about

682
00:28:02,700 --> 00:28:04,980
 only through Jesus' eyes, when he said these words,

683
00:28:04,980 --> 00:28:06,080
 you are salt of the earth,

684
00:28:06,080 --> 00:28:07,940
 what were the things that were on Jesus' mind?

685
00:28:07,940 --> 00:28:09,580
 There would only have been three things

686
00:28:09,580 --> 00:28:11,480
 'cause this is the way salt was in those days.

687
00:28:11,480 --> 00:28:15,620
 The first was that salt had incredible value.

688
00:28:15,620 --> 00:28:20,140
 Salt was a rare and invaluable commodity in those days.

689
00:28:20,140 --> 00:28:22,120
 Such a valuable commodity, in fact,

690
00:28:22,120 --> 00:28:24,340
 that a lot of Roman soldiers were paid,

691
00:28:24,340 --> 00:28:26,920
 not with money, but paid with salt.

692
00:28:26,920 --> 00:28:29,260
 This is where in the West, we get the expression,

693
00:28:29,260 --> 00:28:31,300
 that person's not worth their salt.

694
00:28:31,300 --> 00:28:32,660
 Ever heard that expression?

695
00:28:32,660 --> 00:28:35,820
 It comes from this idea that salt was so valuable

696
00:28:35,820 --> 00:28:38,020
 that soldiers were paid with salt.

697
00:28:38,020 --> 00:28:40,340
 The actual name for it was salarium,

698
00:28:40,340 --> 00:28:43,820
 which is actually where you get the name salary from.

699
00:28:43,820 --> 00:28:47,980
 So this idea, when Jesus says, you are salt of the earth,

700
00:28:47,980 --> 00:28:50,700
 he's like saying, you are the value

701
00:28:50,700 --> 00:28:52,820
 that I place in the world.

702
00:28:52,820 --> 00:28:55,940
 So you have this inherent, beautiful value

703
00:28:55,940 --> 00:28:58,120
 'cause you got the gospel inside of you.

704
00:28:58,120 --> 00:29:00,060
 That same spirit that raised Jesus from the dead

705
00:29:00,060 --> 00:29:01,220
 sits inside of you.

706
00:29:01,220 --> 00:29:03,740
 There's so much value and treasure in you

707
00:29:03,740 --> 00:29:05,200
 and I've placed you in the world.

708
00:29:05,200 --> 00:29:07,860
 So when you remain private,

709
00:29:07,860 --> 00:29:10,580
 with the value that is inside of you,

710
00:29:10,580 --> 00:29:13,580
 not only are you devaluing yourself,

711
00:29:13,580 --> 00:29:15,620
 you're also devaluing the world.

712
00:29:15,620 --> 00:29:17,480
 Think of it this way.

713
00:29:17,480 --> 00:29:21,980
 It's like getting paid a salary, receiving that salary,

714
00:29:21,980 --> 00:29:23,420
 putting it in a bank account,

715
00:29:23,420 --> 00:29:26,380
 never spending or using that salary,

716
00:29:26,380 --> 00:29:28,620
 and then complaining that you're poor.

717
00:29:28,620 --> 00:29:33,220
 This is what Christians do in the world.

718
00:29:33,220 --> 00:29:36,840
 When we are escaping, insulating or conforming,

719
00:29:36,840 --> 00:29:38,120
 here's what we say.

720
00:29:38,120 --> 00:29:42,160
 We have the Christ, the gospel inside of us,

721
00:29:42,160 --> 00:29:44,760
 but we don't do anything with it

722
00:29:44,760 --> 00:29:47,120
 and we still complain that the world's on fire.

723
00:29:47,120 --> 00:29:50,160
 And Jesus stands by you and says,

724
00:29:50,160 --> 00:29:52,160
 you're the salt of the earth.

725
00:29:52,160 --> 00:29:53,520
 You're the value.

726
00:29:53,520 --> 00:29:55,040
 Yes, the gospel is me, not you,

727
00:29:55,040 --> 00:29:57,080
 but that gospel sits inside of you.

728
00:29:57,080 --> 00:29:59,000
 You're now my hands and feet in the world.

729
00:29:59,000 --> 00:30:02,800
 You bring value and if you don't act, if you don't do,

730
00:30:02,800 --> 00:30:06,800
 if you don't be in the world with the values of the kingdom,

731
00:30:06,800 --> 00:30:08,880
 you're devaluing the world

732
00:30:08,880 --> 00:30:10,820
 and you're not doing what you've been called to do.

733
00:30:10,820 --> 00:30:12,300
 It's simple, he's saying.

734
00:30:12,300 --> 00:30:14,420
 Which is really interesting

735
00:30:14,420 --> 00:30:18,640
 because salt was always designed to be placed on something.

736
00:30:18,640 --> 00:30:20,500
 Salt in a salt shaker is useless.

737
00:30:20,500 --> 00:30:21,940
 Think about it this way.

738
00:30:21,940 --> 00:30:25,320
 In the same way that salt that only exists

739
00:30:25,320 --> 00:30:27,840
 in a salt shaker is useless,

740
00:30:27,840 --> 00:30:31,320
 so is a Christian who only exists in the church.

741
00:30:32,320 --> 00:30:34,260
 Come on church, come on.

742
00:30:34,260 --> 00:30:37,160
 In the same way that salt that only exists

743
00:30:37,160 --> 00:30:41,040
 in a salt shaker is never poured out is useless,

744
00:30:41,040 --> 00:30:44,960
 so is a Christian who only exists in the church.

745
00:30:44,960 --> 00:30:48,120
 That's not what the church is here for,

746
00:30:48,120 --> 00:30:51,680
 to just gather us together once a week and make us feel good.

747
00:30:51,680 --> 00:30:54,040
 The church, as it says in Ephesians,

748
00:30:54,040 --> 00:30:57,860
 is the manifold wisdom of God to the world.

749
00:30:57,860 --> 00:31:00,240
 We are to be poured out.

750
00:31:00,240 --> 00:31:01,960
 The second thing Jesus would have thought about

751
00:31:01,960 --> 00:31:03,840
 when he says, "You're the salt of the earth,"

752
00:31:03,840 --> 00:31:06,640
 is that salt was a flavor enhancer,

753
00:31:06,640 --> 00:31:08,480
 much in the same way that we use it a lot today

754
00:31:08,480 --> 00:31:10,360
 when we're cooking food in our homes

755
00:31:10,360 --> 00:31:12,920
 and going to restaurants and having food given to us.

756
00:31:12,920 --> 00:31:15,360
 Salt is a flavor enhancer.

757
00:31:15,360 --> 00:31:17,840
 And not only does it bring its own flavor,

758
00:31:17,840 --> 00:31:19,680
 but salt, when it's used right,

759
00:31:19,680 --> 00:31:22,760
 actually brings the flavor out of the meat itself

760
00:31:22,760 --> 00:31:24,760
 or brings the flavor out of the fish

761
00:31:24,760 --> 00:31:26,700
 or whatever it is that it's on.

762
00:31:26,700 --> 00:31:31,300
 It enhances the flavor that is already contained there.

763
00:31:31,300 --> 00:31:34,220
 So when Jesus says, "You are the salts of the earth,"

764
00:31:34,220 --> 00:31:36,340
 what he's saying is, "You are the ones

765
00:31:36,340 --> 00:31:40,100
 "that I'm sending into the world to bring new flavor

766
00:31:40,100 --> 00:31:43,020
 "and to enhance the flavor of that world."

767
00:31:43,020 --> 00:31:46,260
 Almost like without you, the world is dry,

768
00:31:46,260 --> 00:31:49,700
 it is tasteless, it is bland, it is helpless,

769
00:31:49,700 --> 00:31:52,140
 but you, as the salt of the earth,

770
00:31:52,140 --> 00:31:54,820
 the flavor enhances in the world.

771
00:31:54,820 --> 00:31:57,500
 And when you are active as a Christian

772
00:31:57,500 --> 00:32:00,020
 in the public spheres that I've placed you in,

773
00:32:00,020 --> 00:32:02,820
 you make things taste better.

774
00:32:02,820 --> 00:32:04,540
 You make the world better,

775
00:32:04,540 --> 00:32:08,260
 which is a different way of thinking than these models.

776
00:32:08,260 --> 00:32:10,740
 'Cause in these models, it's like, "The world is terrible.

777
00:32:10,740 --> 00:32:13,580
 "I just need to get out of it."

778
00:32:13,580 --> 00:32:16,760
 When Jesus says, "You are the flavor enhancer of the world,"

779
00:32:16,760 --> 00:32:20,040
 what he's saying to you is, "You better stay in the world

780
00:32:20,040 --> 00:32:22,700
 "because I've created value in the world.

781
00:32:22,700 --> 00:32:26,720
 "I've created beauty and wonder and goodness in the world.

782
00:32:26,720 --> 00:32:30,820
 "But if the Christians are not present, no one will see it.

783
00:32:30,820 --> 00:32:35,080
 "You are salts of the earth."

784
00:32:35,080 --> 00:32:38,060
 Now, if it's true that salt enhances flavor,

785
00:32:38,060 --> 00:32:41,160
 then could it be that one of the reasons

786
00:32:41,160 --> 00:32:45,500
 why we're seeing so much brokenness in the world today

787
00:32:45,500 --> 00:32:49,600
 is not because evil abounds, but because Christians don't?

788
00:32:51,460 --> 00:32:54,500
 When the church falls silent,

789
00:32:54,500 --> 00:32:58,620
 all people are left with is the tastelessness of the world.

790
00:32:58,620 --> 00:32:59,540
 Come on, church.

791
00:32:59,540 --> 00:33:02,940
 When the church stays silent,

792
00:33:02,940 --> 00:33:06,240
 all there is left is the tastelessness of this world.

793
00:33:06,240 --> 00:33:08,420
 You are salts.

794
00:33:08,420 --> 00:33:09,700
 The third thing he would have thought about

795
00:33:09,700 --> 00:33:12,900
 is that salt was a preservative agent.

796
00:33:12,900 --> 00:33:15,780
 It was the very thing that in an age before refrigeration

797
00:33:15,780 --> 00:33:17,940
 and ice, at least in the Middle East,

798
00:33:17,940 --> 00:33:21,660
 they had no way of preserving the food from decay,

799
00:33:21,660 --> 00:33:23,980
 natural decay and natural going off.

800
00:33:23,980 --> 00:33:26,460
 So salt was used to pack around meat

801
00:33:26,460 --> 00:33:29,860
 or pack around lamb or pack around fish

802
00:33:29,860 --> 00:33:32,460
 to preserve it for the long time

803
00:33:32,460 --> 00:33:34,140
 in an age before refrigeration.

804
00:33:34,140 --> 00:33:35,900
 So when Jesus says to the disciples,

805
00:33:35,900 --> 00:33:37,660
 "You are the salt of the earth,"

806
00:33:37,660 --> 00:33:40,320
 what he's saying is, "You're the preservative agents

807
00:33:40,320 --> 00:33:41,420
 "that I am releasing.

808
00:33:41,420 --> 00:33:45,620
 "I'm literally packing around the culture, around the world

809
00:33:45,620 --> 00:33:48,820
 "so that the world does not decay."

810
00:33:48,820 --> 00:33:50,940
 Like, I don't wanna see the world decay.

811
00:33:50,940 --> 00:33:53,700
 I don't wanna see the world dark and blank.

812
00:33:53,700 --> 00:33:56,100
 I don't wanna see evil abound.

813
00:33:56,100 --> 00:33:58,220
 I wanna see the church rise up.

814
00:33:58,220 --> 00:33:59,380
 And when you rise up,

815
00:33:59,380 --> 00:34:01,540
 it's like you're the preservative agent,

816
00:34:01,540 --> 00:34:05,500
 which ensures that the culture and the world does not decay.

817
00:34:05,500 --> 00:34:08,980
 'Cause look, I'm not gonna bungee jump you out of here

818
00:34:08,980 --> 00:34:11,140
 so you can go sit on a fluffy cloud.

819
00:34:11,140 --> 00:34:15,020
 No, the prayer I taught you is heaven come to earth.

820
00:34:15,020 --> 00:34:17,620
 And the picture in Revelations 21 and 22

821
00:34:17,620 --> 00:34:20,460
 is a new Jerusalem coming to earth.

822
00:34:20,460 --> 00:34:21,640
 And Jesus says these things,

823
00:34:21,640 --> 00:34:26,640
 "Behold, I make all things new, not all new things."

824
00:34:26,640 --> 00:34:33,820
 So you're the preservative agents of a world

825
00:34:33,820 --> 00:34:36,660
 that is desperately in decline

826
00:34:36,660 --> 00:34:39,660
 when you keep your mouth and life shut.

827
00:34:39,660 --> 00:34:42,300
 Think about this.

828
00:34:43,260 --> 00:34:46,060
 When Christians remain private in their faith,

829
00:34:46,060 --> 00:34:49,060
 they contribute to the decaying of the world.

830
00:34:49,060 --> 00:34:53,340
 It's pretty strong.

831
00:34:53,340 --> 00:34:55,540
 So Jesus lays this all out.

832
00:34:55,540 --> 00:34:58,100
 And then he says, "You're light of the world."

833
00:34:58,100 --> 00:34:59,060
 Which is fascinating

834
00:34:59,060 --> 00:35:00,660
 because when he says, "You're light of the world,"

835
00:35:00,660 --> 00:35:03,340
 later on, he's gonna say, "I'm the light of the world."

836
00:35:03,340 --> 00:35:05,500
 But here he says, "You're the light of the world."

837
00:35:05,500 --> 00:35:06,340
 What he's saying is,

838
00:35:06,340 --> 00:35:09,140
 here's what happens when you go into the public spheres

839
00:35:09,140 --> 00:35:11,900
 with your faith, again, sharing the gospel,

840
00:35:11,900 --> 00:35:13,780
 but also living the values of the kingdom

841
00:35:13,780 --> 00:35:14,980
 publicly before you.

842
00:35:14,980 --> 00:35:16,700
 When you do that, he's saying,

843
00:35:16,700 --> 00:35:19,620
 "It's like you're shining a bright bolt of lightning

844
00:35:19,620 --> 00:35:21,860
 into the darkness that is around."

845
00:35:21,860 --> 00:35:23,560
 And here's what that light does.

846
00:35:23,560 --> 00:35:27,420
 Yes, number one, it shines a light on what is broken

847
00:35:27,420 --> 00:35:30,300
 and decaying and what is evil and sin

848
00:35:30,300 --> 00:35:33,820
 and helps people to see that they can repent

849
00:35:33,820 --> 00:35:35,460
 and find new life in Christ.

850
00:35:35,460 --> 00:35:36,860
 Absolutely.

851
00:35:36,860 --> 00:35:40,180
 When we share the gospel and live the gospel publicly,

852
00:35:40,180 --> 00:35:42,060
 we are inviting people in to realize

853
00:35:42,060 --> 00:35:44,120
 that the way that they are living right now is not right,

854
00:35:44,120 --> 00:35:46,260
 but that there is a loving and faithful God

855
00:35:46,260 --> 00:35:48,100
 who will forgive them in repentance

856
00:35:48,100 --> 00:35:49,860
 and birth them into new life.

857
00:35:49,860 --> 00:35:54,380
 But it also means that when the light shines

858
00:35:54,380 --> 00:35:57,220
 through a church that moves publicly in his faith,

859
00:35:57,220 --> 00:35:59,740
 the things that are good in the world

860
00:35:59,740 --> 00:36:02,100
 that people prior to that could not see

861
00:36:02,100 --> 00:36:04,700
 are illuminated again for them.

862
00:36:04,700 --> 00:36:07,100
 That the hopelessness that people feel,

863
00:36:07,100 --> 00:36:09,780
 the way of looking and saying, "Nobody here is good.

864
00:36:09,780 --> 00:36:10,740
 Nobody loves me.

865
00:36:10,740 --> 00:36:11,780
 Everybody hates me.

866
00:36:11,780 --> 00:36:12,620
 Everybody is..."

867
00:36:12,620 --> 00:36:14,820
 When we as Christians begin to show love,

868
00:36:14,820 --> 00:36:17,500
 live love, be love to the ones around us

869
00:36:17,500 --> 00:36:19,780
 who are so darkened by the brokenness around them,

870
00:36:19,780 --> 00:36:22,500
 they can begin to see that there is hope.

871
00:36:22,500 --> 00:36:24,900
 Hope in Jesus Christ first and foremost,

872
00:36:24,900 --> 00:36:28,500
 and hope in the world and the body that he's created.

873
00:36:28,500 --> 00:36:33,140
 It's beautiful invitation to be this light.

874
00:36:33,140 --> 00:36:37,580
 So when the world goes crazy and we're tempted to think

875
00:36:37,580 --> 00:36:39,820
 that it's either to privatize ourself,

876
00:36:39,820 --> 00:36:42,300
 to escape or insulate or conform,

877
00:36:42,300 --> 00:36:45,020
 we have to realize that, no, we've been called to engage,

878
00:36:45,020 --> 00:36:48,140
 but not engage in a way that takes worldly power

879
00:36:48,140 --> 00:36:50,300
 and dresses it up in the name of Jesus

880
00:36:50,300 --> 00:36:53,580
 and tries to control from the top down,

881
00:36:53,580 --> 00:36:56,700
 but a world in which we as the salt and light

882
00:36:56,700 --> 00:36:58,420
 move from the bottom up,

883
00:36:58,420 --> 00:37:03,340
 offering hope and preservation and flavor enhancement

884
00:37:03,340 --> 00:37:05,740
 and shining light so that people can see

885
00:37:05,740 --> 00:37:08,220
 and the world begins to shift and change.

886
00:37:08,220 --> 00:37:09,780
 One of my favorite New Testament scholars

887
00:37:09,780 --> 00:37:12,140
 is a guy by the name of Craig Blomberg.

888
00:37:12,140 --> 00:37:13,740
 He's brilliant on the parables

889
00:37:13,740 --> 00:37:16,300
 and he's written on this idea of salt and light.

890
00:37:16,300 --> 00:37:18,380
 Let me read you what he writes.

891
00:37:18,380 --> 00:37:20,540
 He says, "Both the metaphors of salt and light

892
00:37:20,540 --> 00:37:22,420
 raise important challenges

893
00:37:22,420 --> 00:37:25,180
 about Christian involvement in society.

894
00:37:25,180 --> 00:37:28,440
 We are not called to control secular power structures,

895
00:37:28,440 --> 00:37:30,940
 neither are we promised that we can Christianize

896
00:37:30,940 --> 00:37:33,260
 the legislation and values of the world.

897
00:37:33,260 --> 00:37:37,660
 Instead, we must remain active, preservative agents,

898
00:37:37,660 --> 00:37:40,140
 indeed irritants," love that word,

899
00:37:40,140 --> 00:37:42,900
 "in calling and revealing to the world

900
00:37:42,900 --> 00:37:44,780
 God's heart of love."

901
00:37:44,780 --> 00:37:48,100
 We are active, preservative agents

902
00:37:48,100 --> 00:37:51,180
 of a world that God has created and that He loves so much.

903
00:37:51,180 --> 00:37:55,220
 We are irritants to the evil and the sin

904
00:37:55,220 --> 00:37:56,660
 and the brokenness of this world,

905
00:37:56,660 --> 00:37:59,980
 to the injustice which grasps a hold of so many people.

906
00:37:59,980 --> 00:38:03,140
 We get to live a better model

907
00:38:03,140 --> 00:38:04,900
 and Jesus points to what that is

908
00:38:04,900 --> 00:38:07,580
 right at the end of verse 16 here.

909
00:38:07,580 --> 00:38:09,460
 He says this, "In the same way,

910
00:38:09,460 --> 00:38:12,700
 let your light shine before people that they may see,"

911
00:38:12,700 --> 00:38:15,580
 what? "Your good deeds."

912
00:38:15,580 --> 00:38:18,300
 So what's Jesus' model?

913
00:38:18,300 --> 00:38:20,660
 It's not escape, it's not insulate, it's not control,

914
00:38:20,660 --> 00:38:22,260
 it's not conform.

915
00:38:22,260 --> 00:38:24,180
 What Jesus is saying, there's another way

916
00:38:24,180 --> 00:38:29,180
 and here's the summary of that way, "Your good deeds."

917
00:38:29,180 --> 00:38:31,460
 In the Greek, if you translate these words,

918
00:38:31,460 --> 00:38:35,140
 it means this, beautiful or lovely works.

919
00:38:35,140 --> 00:38:38,220
 Not talking about moral good,

920
00:38:38,220 --> 00:38:43,220
 talking about wonder and creativity and beauty and love.

921
00:38:43,220 --> 00:38:46,020
 He's like, "The deeds you do

922
00:38:46,020 --> 00:38:48,700
 that brings my beauty to the world."

923
00:38:48,700 --> 00:38:52,540
 Now, what are those deeds?

924
00:38:52,540 --> 00:38:55,780
 Well, it's interesting 'cause Jesus starts this section

925
00:38:55,780 --> 00:38:57,500
 we're looking at with a direct thing.

926
00:38:57,500 --> 00:38:58,980
 He says, "You are the salt."

927
00:38:58,980 --> 00:39:00,300
 He says, "You are the light."

928
00:39:00,300 --> 00:39:01,260
 And right at the end, He says,

929
00:39:01,260 --> 00:39:03,300
 "Because you're doing these deeds.

930
00:39:03,300 --> 00:39:05,980
 And when you do these deeds, people will glorify Jesus."

931
00:39:05,980 --> 00:39:06,820
 And so we're left to say,

932
00:39:06,820 --> 00:39:10,140
 "Well, what are those deeds, Jesus?"

933
00:39:10,140 --> 00:39:11,820
 Well, He's already answered that

934
00:39:11,820 --> 00:39:13,540
 before He even gets to this passage.

935
00:39:13,540 --> 00:39:15,500
 So let's jump back and have a look at what He says

936
00:39:15,500 --> 00:39:17,380
 right at the beginning of the chapter

937
00:39:17,380 --> 00:39:19,380
 in verse three of chapter five.

938
00:39:19,380 --> 00:39:21,900
 "Blessed are the poor in spirit,

939
00:39:21,900 --> 00:39:23,660
 for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.

940
00:39:23,660 --> 00:39:26,060
 Blessed are those who mourn, for they will be comforted.

941
00:39:26,060 --> 00:39:28,660
 Blessed are the meek, for they will inherit the earth.

942
00:39:28,660 --> 00:39:31,220
 Blessed are those who hunger and thirst for righteousness,

943
00:39:31,220 --> 00:39:32,420
 for they will be filled.

944
00:39:32,420 --> 00:39:35,180
 Blessed are the merciful, for they will be shown mercy.

945
00:39:35,180 --> 00:39:37,900
 Blessed are the pure in heart, for they will see God.

946
00:39:37,900 --> 00:39:40,020
 Blessed are the peacemakers,

947
00:39:40,020 --> 00:39:42,740
 for they will be called sons and daughters of God.

948
00:39:42,740 --> 00:39:44,540
 Blessed are those who are persecuted

949
00:39:44,540 --> 00:39:45,860
 because of righteousness,

950
00:39:45,860 --> 00:39:48,100
 for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.

951
00:39:48,100 --> 00:39:51,900
 Blessed are you when people insult you, persecute you,

952
00:39:51,900 --> 00:39:54,980
 falsely say all kinds of evil against you because of me.

953
00:39:54,980 --> 00:39:56,780
 Rejoice and be glad,

954
00:39:56,780 --> 00:39:59,580
 because great is your reward in heaven.

955
00:39:59,580 --> 00:40:02,220
 For in the same way they persecuted the prophets

956
00:40:02,220 --> 00:40:03,500
 who were before you."

957
00:40:03,500 --> 00:40:06,460
 You are the salt of the earth.

958
00:40:06,460 --> 00:40:10,180
 You are the, in other words, what he's saying is,

959
00:40:10,180 --> 00:40:14,580
 being salt and light is not a command, it's a response.

960
00:40:14,580 --> 00:40:19,100
 It's a response out of what we are doing

961
00:40:19,100 --> 00:40:20,980
 as we live our faith more publicly.

962
00:40:20,980 --> 00:40:23,340
 And what does it mean to live our faith publicly?

963
00:40:23,340 --> 00:40:24,820
 It means to mourn with those who mourn.

964
00:40:24,820 --> 00:40:26,420
 It means to stand with the peacemakers.

965
00:40:26,420 --> 00:40:27,540
 It means to be merciful.

966
00:40:27,540 --> 00:40:29,100
 It means all of the things that we just read

967
00:40:29,100 --> 00:40:29,940
 in the Beatitudes,

968
00:40:29,940 --> 00:40:32,740
 that does not sound like escaping, insulating, conforming,

969
00:40:32,740 --> 00:40:35,220
 and it definitely doesn't sound like controlling.

970
00:40:35,220 --> 00:40:37,780
 It sounds like a better way.

971
00:40:37,780 --> 00:40:40,420
 Now, when we read the Beatitudes,

972
00:40:40,420 --> 00:40:42,700
 we often read it like this, that I need,

973
00:40:42,700 --> 00:40:45,140
 if God blesses these kinds of people,

974
00:40:45,140 --> 00:40:47,460
 the poor in spirit, the meek,

975
00:40:47,460 --> 00:40:49,180
 the ones that are peacemakers,

976
00:40:49,180 --> 00:40:52,700
 then I need to be those people and God will bless me.

977
00:40:52,700 --> 00:40:54,100
 So oftentimes when we read the Beatitudes,

978
00:40:54,100 --> 00:40:56,460
 we put ourselves in the position

979
00:40:56,460 --> 00:40:58,500
 of the person who's getting blessed.

980
00:40:58,500 --> 00:40:59,580
 Do you follow that?

981
00:40:59,580 --> 00:41:00,700
 So I just need to be more meek.

982
00:41:00,700 --> 00:41:02,180
 I just need to be, this is the kind of person

983
00:41:02,180 --> 00:41:04,020
 I need to be to get God's blessing.

984
00:41:04,020 --> 00:41:06,060
 When Jesus says, you are the salt of the world,

985
00:41:06,060 --> 00:41:07,180
 you are the light of the world,

986
00:41:07,180 --> 00:41:09,140
 because you're doing these beautiful, lovely deeds.

987
00:41:09,140 --> 00:41:11,220
 What Jesus is saying at the beginning of the Beatitudes

988
00:41:11,220 --> 00:41:12,060
 is actually different.

989
00:41:12,060 --> 00:41:14,700
 He's not saying, be the one who is the meek

990
00:41:14,700 --> 00:41:15,620
 and the mild person.

991
00:41:15,620 --> 00:41:17,860
 He's saying, here's the role of the church.

992
00:41:17,860 --> 00:41:19,660
 Here's the role of the Christian.

993
00:41:19,660 --> 00:41:23,540
 You are the ones to bless the peacemakers.

994
00:41:23,540 --> 00:41:25,980
 You are the ones to bless the meek.

995
00:41:25,980 --> 00:41:28,580
 You are the ones to bless those who mourn.

996
00:41:28,580 --> 00:41:31,260
 You are the ones to bless those who hunger

997
00:41:31,260 --> 00:41:32,820
 and thirst for righteousness.

998
00:41:32,820 --> 00:41:36,300
 You're the ones who do these lovely, beautiful things

999
00:41:36,300 --> 00:41:39,180
 of blessing as I would bless

1000
00:41:39,180 --> 00:41:41,500
 when the church moves in my heart,

1001
00:41:41,500 --> 00:41:43,540
 when the church moves in my spirit

1002
00:41:43,540 --> 00:41:45,700
 and comes around those who are hurting and broken

1003
00:41:45,700 --> 00:41:48,460
 and vulnerable and marginalized and seeks to bless,

1004
00:41:48,460 --> 00:41:51,140
 seeks to love, seeks to offer grace.

1005
00:41:51,140 --> 00:41:54,900
 This is what changes the darkness in the light.

1006
00:41:54,900 --> 00:41:58,580
 This is what takes the world and brings its flavor.

1007
00:41:58,580 --> 00:42:00,940
 You are the ones to bless.

1008
00:42:00,940 --> 00:42:05,020
 Those are the lovely deeds, the good deeds,

1009
00:42:05,020 --> 00:42:08,620
 the beautiful deeds that when people see you do it,

1010
00:42:08,620 --> 00:42:11,220
 their inclination is not you're amazing.

1011
00:42:11,220 --> 00:42:15,780
 Their inclination is I never knew God was like that.

1012
00:42:15,780 --> 00:42:23,060
 So when we hear rhetoric about hate coming from the church,

1013
00:42:23,500 --> 00:42:26,980
 when we see rhetoric about power and control

1014
00:42:26,980 --> 00:42:30,380
 and top down coming from the church,

1015
00:42:30,380 --> 00:42:36,260
 we have to sit again in these profound words of Jesus

1016
00:42:36,260 --> 00:42:39,460
 and think again about what it means to not be privates,

1017
00:42:39,460 --> 00:42:40,460
 but to be public,

1018
00:42:40,460 --> 00:42:44,580
 but not in a way that leads to some Christian nationalism,

1019
00:42:44,580 --> 00:42:46,660
 but in a way that offers the gospel

1020
00:42:46,660 --> 00:42:49,340
 as Jesus always intended it to be offered.

1021
00:42:49,340 --> 00:42:53,300
 To those that desperately need it,

1022
00:42:53,300 --> 00:42:56,300
 shining light in the darkness of sin,

1023
00:42:56,300 --> 00:42:58,980
 shining light into the goodness of the world,

1024
00:42:58,980 --> 00:43:03,540
 preserving, enhancing, creating value.

1025
00:43:03,540 --> 00:43:06,740
 That my friends is the church alive,

1026
00:43:06,740 --> 00:43:08,700
 but the church is only alive

1027
00:43:08,700 --> 00:43:12,260
 when we decide to move from a place of privacy in our faith

1028
00:43:12,260 --> 00:43:14,660
 to a place of living for Christ as he called us to.

1029
00:43:14,660 --> 00:43:16,140
 And over the next seven weeks,

1030
00:43:16,140 --> 00:43:17,660
 that's what we're gonna unpack

1031
00:43:17,660 --> 00:43:19,740
 in all the areas of your lives.

1032
00:43:19,740 --> 00:43:20,580
 Amen.

1033
00:43:20,580 --> 00:43:21,420
 - Amen.

1034
00:43:21,420 --> 00:43:22,260
 - Could you stand with me?

1035
00:43:22,260 --> 00:43:23,780
 I would love to pray with you.

1036
00:43:23,780 --> 00:43:29,380
 Father, I thank you so much

1037
00:43:29,380 --> 00:43:32,020
 for each person here in this room,

1038
00:43:32,020 --> 00:43:35,660
 in our overflow, those that are watching online right now.

1039
00:43:35,660 --> 00:43:39,580
 Father, we pray, we come to you in prayer,

1040
00:43:39,580 --> 00:43:41,660
 recognizing at the start of this seven weeks

1041
00:43:41,660 --> 00:43:44,260
 that we are desperate for this new model.

1042
00:43:44,260 --> 00:43:48,060
 Grateful that you look at us and speak over us

1043
00:43:48,060 --> 00:43:50,700
 and say you are salt, you are light.

1044
00:43:51,060 --> 00:43:53,140
 (gentle music)

1045
00:43:53,140 --> 00:43:55,180
 Father, would you help us where we recognize

1046
00:43:55,180 --> 00:43:57,780
 that the escape, insulate, control and conform

1047
00:43:57,780 --> 00:44:00,340
 is still well and alive in the global church,

1048
00:44:00,340 --> 00:44:02,700
 is still well and alive inside of me,

1049
00:44:02,700 --> 00:44:04,540
 and I'm sure many of us in this room.

1050
00:44:04,540 --> 00:44:09,860
 Lord, would you help us to not just see

1051
00:44:09,860 --> 00:44:11,180
 that there's a better way,

1052
00:44:11,180 --> 00:44:13,180
 but begin to walk in a better way.

1053
00:44:13,180 --> 00:44:17,860
 And Father, where we're tempted to,

1054
00:44:18,740 --> 00:44:23,740
 in a time like this, ironically, keep our faith more quiet.

1055
00:44:23,740 --> 00:44:27,420
 Father, I pray you would light a fire

1056
00:44:27,420 --> 00:44:28,580
 in people in this room,

1057
00:44:28,580 --> 00:44:32,180
 to have the urgency,

1058
00:44:32,180 --> 00:44:37,060
 the urgency not to escape, to insulate,

1059
00:44:37,060 --> 00:44:40,660
 to control or conform,

1060
00:44:40,660 --> 00:44:43,940
 but the urgency to serve like you served,

1061
00:44:43,940 --> 00:44:48,900
 the urgency to wash the feet of the people around us,

1062
00:44:48,900 --> 00:44:51,780
 the urgency to love our enemy,

1063
00:44:51,780 --> 00:44:54,580
 the urgency to offer grace,

1064
00:44:54,580 --> 00:44:56,260
 the urgency to mourn,

1065
00:44:56,260 --> 00:44:58,980
 the urgency to bless the peacemakers,

1066
00:44:58,980 --> 00:45:01,180
 the urgency to reach out to the people

1067
00:45:01,180 --> 00:45:03,780
 that the rest of society seems to be condemning

1068
00:45:03,780 --> 00:45:05,180
 and ignoring and avoiding.

1069
00:45:05,180 --> 00:45:08,900
 Would you give us an urgency to be like you?

1070
00:45:09,740 --> 00:45:12,340
 (gentle music)

1071
00:45:12,340 --> 00:45:15,660
 I just want you to take a moment

1072
00:45:15,660 --> 00:45:17,460
 just in the quietness of your heart.

1073
00:45:17,460 --> 00:45:20,260
 Maybe there's a confession for you to bring

1074
00:45:20,260 --> 00:45:21,260
 to the Lord today,

1075
00:45:21,260 --> 00:45:25,020
 as Jesus is present with you now.

1076
00:45:25,020 --> 00:45:26,580
 No condemnation that comes,

1077
00:45:26,580 --> 00:45:28,660
 he's not whacking you with a stick,

1078
00:45:28,660 --> 00:45:31,580
 but there is this beautiful sense of conviction

1079
00:45:31,580 --> 00:45:32,460
 that does come,

1080
00:45:32,460 --> 00:45:37,260
 when we realize that we've drifted from being salt and light,

1081
00:45:38,700 --> 00:45:41,860
 where we realize that we've decided to embed ourselves more

1082
00:45:41,860 --> 00:45:46,860
 in the privacy and the personal nature of our faith.

1083
00:45:46,860 --> 00:45:50,660
 And perhaps your prayer today is just to ask the Lord

1084
00:45:50,660 --> 00:45:52,380
 to forgive you for that natural tendency

1085
00:45:52,380 --> 00:45:53,380
 that you might have.

1086
00:45:53,380 --> 00:45:59,180
 Ask him to show you how you can break

1087
00:45:59,180 --> 00:46:01,540
 the temptation to privacy in this time,

1088
00:46:01,540 --> 00:46:06,540
 and then invite him to strengthen your courage,

1089
00:46:07,820 --> 00:46:09,980
 to strengthen your resolve,

1090
00:46:09,980 --> 00:46:15,780
 and to show you once again, the beautiful, lovely deeds.

1091
00:46:15,780 --> 00:46:19,300
 The simple things this week that you can do,

1092
00:46:19,300 --> 00:46:22,980
 to serve as Jesus would serve,

1093
00:46:22,980 --> 00:46:26,380
 to make the world a better place.

1094
00:46:26,380 --> 00:46:28,700
 Father, we thank you that this gospel of yours

1095
00:46:28,700 --> 00:46:29,940
 is counter-cultural.

1096
00:46:29,940 --> 00:46:33,380
 On the surface, it sounds weak,

1097
00:46:35,300 --> 00:46:37,220
 but Lord, this gospel of yours

1098
00:46:37,220 --> 00:46:40,460
 means that there is no other name

1099
00:46:40,460 --> 00:46:41,940
 that is higher than your name.

1100
00:46:41,940 --> 00:46:45,620
 As we sang in that song earlier,

1101
00:46:45,620 --> 00:46:47,620
 that we would take the place of suffering

1102
00:46:47,620 --> 00:46:49,060
 so that we would rise in you.

1103
00:46:49,060 --> 00:46:52,980
 Lord, I pray that in this time where the world has gone crazy

1104
00:46:52,980 --> 00:46:55,660
 we would not escape, we would not insulate,

1105
00:46:55,660 --> 00:47:00,660
 we would reign in the fear that drives control.

1106
00:47:03,380 --> 00:47:08,380
 And we would stand against the conformity that comes,

1107
00:47:08,380 --> 00:47:12,100
 and we'd be salt and light again.

1108
00:47:12,100 --> 00:47:16,020
 We thank you for this in Jesus' name.

1109
00:47:16,020 --> 00:47:17,700
 Everyone says, amen.

1110
00:47:17,700 --> 00:47:19,460
 Let's continue to worship together.

1111
00:47:19,460 --> 00:47:22,060
 (gentle music)

1112
00:47:22,060 --> 00:47:32,060
 [BLANK_AUDIO]

